    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available is a museum-grade 2004 BMW M3 (E46) finished in Carbon Black. This specimen is powered by the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six, featuring individual throttle bodies and a 7,900 RPM redline. The drivetrain is anchored by a precise 6-speed Getrag manual transmission and a variable M differential lock. This vehicle has undergone comprehensive preventative maintenance, including a professional VANOS overhaul and rod bearing replacement. The rear subframe has been inspected and reinforced, ensuring structural rigidity. The suspension remains factory-spec with crisp turn-in, and the original Laguna Seca Blue interior shows zero bolster wear. This is a turn-key collector piece for the discerning purist demanding mechanical perfection.",
